Kalisha.NaickerPhoto: supplied The Beehive teachers and pupils at the SPCA. Multimedia &nbsp; &nbsp; User Galleries &nbsp; &nbsp; News in Pictures Send us your pictures &nbsp; &nbsp; Send us your stories BEEHIVE Pre-School little ones visited the Kloof and Highway SPCA last week, accompanied by their mom and dad, teachers and principal. Even though these little children are only three, four and five years of age, they collected and donated dog and cat food for the animals in the SPCA care. The children also enjoyed an educational puppet show. - Supplied.24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.